-- Carlyle's Rubenstein Prefers Private Equity Deals of $3 Billion-$7 Billion
-- B y   A r i f   S h a r i f
-- 2010-10-19T07:15:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-19/carlyle-s-rubenstein-prefers-private-equity-deals-of-3-billion-7-billion.html
David Rubenstein, co-founder of the
Carlyle Group, said he preferred private equity deals in the
range of $3 billion to $7 billion as bigger transactions may not
necessarily be better. Rubenstein was speaking in Abu Dhabi
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
